  "prompt": "What are some good colleges in India that I can still apply to their MBA program for this year\u2019s session?",
  "response": "While specific deadlines for MBA programs can vary from year to year, there are several esteemed institutions in India where you might still be able to apply for MBA programs in late fall or early winter. Some of these include:\n\n1. **Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs)**: Various IIMs accept applications till December through the Common Admission Test (CAT).\n    - IIM Ahmedabad\n    - IIM Bangalore\n    - IIM Calcutta\n    - IIM Lucknow\n    - IIM Indore\n    - IIM Kozhikode\n\n2. **XLRI Jamshedpur**: The Xavier School of Management offers programs in Business Management and Human Resource Management. Applications for the XAT (Xavier Aptitude Test) are usually open until November or December.\n\n3. **SP Jain Institute of Management and Research, Mumbai**: SPJIMR might have deadlines extending into December for their postgraduate programs.\n\n4. **Faculty of Management Studies (FMS), Delhi University**: FMS tends to have an application window open till November or December.\n\n5. **Indian School of Business (ISB), Hyderabad and Mohali**: ISB offers a one-year MBA program. They have multiple application rounds, with some deadlines extending into late fall.\n\n6. **Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies (NMIMS), Mumbai**: NMIMS conducts NMAT exams which have late application deadlines, often extending into December.\n\n7. **Great Lakes Institute of Management, Chennai**: Great Lakes offers one-year and two-year programs and generally has application deadlines till December for the program starting the following year.\n\n8. **Symbiosis Institute of Business Management (SIBM), Pune**: SIBM accepts applications through the SNAP test, with the application process generally extending into December.\n\n9. **Institute of Management Technology (IMT), Ghaziabad**: IMT often has deadlines into December or January for their MBA programs.\n\nIt's important to check directly with the institutions for the exact deadlines and requirements for the current year as they can change and some institutes may offer additional rounds or extensions. Always ensure to prepare your applications, required entrance exams (like CAT, XAT, NMAT, etc.), and supporting documents well in advance.",
